.TH "kernel_sendmsg" 9 "kernel_sendmsg" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
kernel_sendmsg \- send a message through @sock (kernel-space)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" kernel_sendmsg
.BI "(struct socket *sock "  ","
.BI "struct msghdr *msg "  ","
.BI "struct kvec *vec "  ","
.BI "size_t num "  ","
.BI "size_t size "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "sock" 12
socket
.IP "msg" 12
message header
.IP "vec" 12
kernel vec
.IP "num" 12
vec array length
.IP "size" 12
total message data size

Builds the message data with \fIvec\fP and sends it through \fIsock\fP.
Returns the number of bytes sent, or an error code.
